  "A higher discount rate makes the present value of a future cash flow:": "",
  "Lower": "",
  "Unpredictable": "",
  "Higher": "",
  "Unchanged": "",
  "PV = FV / (1 + r)^n. A higher discount rate (r) means dividing by a larger number, which reduces the present value. Future money is discounted more heavily when alternative returns are higher.": "",
