  "What is present value (PV)?": "",
  "The total amount of interest earned over time": "",
  "The amount of money in a bank account right now": "",
  "The price of a stock today": "",
  "The current worth of a future sum of money, discounted at an appropriate rate": "",
  "Present value is the current equivalent of a future amount of money, calculated by discounting it back at an appropriate interest or discount rate using the formula PV = FV / (1 + r)^n.": "",
  "What is future value (FV)?": "",
  "The amount a present sum will grow to at a given interest rate over a specified period": "",
  "The original amount of an investment before interest": "",
  "The price prediction for a stock next year": "",
  "The inflation-adjusted value of money": "",
  "Future value is the amount that a present sum of money will be worth at a future date, given a specific rate of return, calculated using FV = PV x (1 + r)^n.": "",
  "What does the discount rate represent in TVM calculations?": "",
  "The opportunity cost of capital -- the return you could earn on an alternative investment of similar risk": "",
  "The Federal Reserve's interest rate without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "The bank's prime lending rate, especially during periods of significant change": "",
  "A markdown on retail prices without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "The discount rate reflects opportunity cost -- the return you could earn if you invested the money elsewhere. It is used to convert future cash flows into their present-day equivalent.": "",
