  "A loan that never needs to be repaid": "",
  "An annuity that lasts exactly 30 years": "",
  "A bond that matures in one year": "",
  "A stream of equal payments that continues forever, with PV = Payment / r": "",
  "A perpetuity is an annuity with no end date -- it pays a fixed amount forever. Its present value is simply PV = Payment / r, where r is the discount rate.": "",
